value.title: Undecided voters call Trump ‘unhinged’ and ‘un-American’ — but unswayed by debate
value.excerpt: After watching the first presidential debate Tuesday night, undecided voters from battleground states across the country still had plenty they wanted to know about coronavirus, racial injustice and what each candidate would do to unite the country.

value.title: Biden: 'He's the racist'
value.excerpt: During the first presidential debate, President Donald Trump claimed he ended racial sensitivity training because it was "racist" and Joe Biden responded that Trump is the racist.

value.title: Ross asked if ending census earlier would produce numbers in Trump's current term
value.excerpt: Commerce Secretary Wilbur Ross' surprise decision Monday evening to end 2020 census counting on October 5 risks an incomplete tally of as many as 10 states, including Florida and Georgia, according to Census Bureau officials.

value.title: Biden paid nearly $300,000 in federal income taxes in 2019
value.excerpt: Joe Biden released his 2019 tax returns on Tuesday, which show he and his wife, Jill, paid nearly $300,000 in federal income tax last year and had an adjusted gross income of about $985,000.

value.title: Barr accused of 'working hand in glove' with Team Trump, White House
value.excerpt: One former federal prosecutor said of Barr, "The attorney general is working hand in glove with the White House and the Trump re-election campaign."

value.title: Facebook and Twitter keep fact-checking Trump on voting by mail. He's undeterred.
value.excerpt: The president has taken full advantage of the policies of Twitter and Facebook to spread election misinformation, making warning labels seem quaint in comparison.

value.title: 'Deeply unpatriotic': Mary Trump slams the president for not paying taxes for years
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump's niece, Mary Trump, say the topic of her uncle not paying income taxes for 10 of the last 15 years must be “hammered on” during the first general election debate Tuesday night.

value.title: Does Trump's 'tightening financial vise' create a security risk?
value.excerpt: Trump holding onto power might be one of the few options he has remaining to prevent his creditors from seizing his personal assets.

value.title: Trump's Supreme Court pick on Capitol Hill for meeting with GOP senators
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump's nominee for the Supreme Court, Judge Amy Coney Barrett, will meet Republican senators throughout Tuesday on Capitol Hill, as the party finalizes plans for a quick confirmation process ahead of the November presidential election.

value.title: Trump administration warns Iraq it plans to shut U.S. Embassy in Baghdad after rocket attacks
value.excerpt: In an interview with NBC News, a top U.S. general recently praised the work of Iraqi security forces protecting American interests in Iraq.

value.title: Trump announces plan to deploy 150 million Covid rapid tests previously touted
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump formally announced a plan on Monday to disperse the 150 million rapid coronavirus tests first promoted by the White House in August.

value.title: Donald Trump Was the Real Winner of ‘The Apprentice’
value.excerpt: The reality show temporarily revived his business fortunes by creating the illusion that he was already doing great.

value.title: Pence tells Americans to 'anticipate that cases will rise' with more coronavirus testing
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence said that "the American people should anticipate that cases will rise" as efforts for increased coronavirus testing are implemented and states in the Midwest are experiencing a surge.

value.title: Kamala Harris says appointing Amy Coney Barrett to the Supreme Court would imperil health care and abortion rights.
value.excerpt: Senator Kamala Harris warns of far-reaching consequences to American society if Judge Amy Coney Barrett is confirmed to the Supreme Court.

value.title: Engage or Proceed? Debating Trump, the Unpredictable Aggressor
value.excerpt: Joe Biden has the scouting report of the president’s past debates and four years in office. One way to use it? Respond to unpredictability with a simple, “Here’s my stability plan.”

value.title: End the Filibuster? Pack the Court? The Left Is Pushing Biden
value.excerpt: A party that is increasingly seeking to play by different rules is led by a figure who helped create the current ones. The outcome of the fight will help define the Democratic Party going forward.

value.title: Former Florida Supreme Court chief justice during 2000 recount warns Trump poses 'grave and real threat to democracy'
value.excerpt: The former chief justice of the Florida Supreme Court is warning that President Donald Trump poses a "grave and real threat to our democracy" because of his threat to not accept the outcome of the election.

value.title: ‘Fox & Friends,’ With Donald Trump Jr., Tries to Dismiss Times Tax Article
value.excerpt: The Fox News morning show, a reliable forum for the president and his defenders, serves up criticism of the report and attacks on Joe Biden.

value.title: Analysis: Tax bombshell reveals Trump's image is a sham
value.excerpt: It was the moment when Donald Trump's "Art of the Deal" fabulism, billionaire tycoon bluster and populist standard-bearing for forgotten Americans was revealed to be what it always looked like: a sham.

value.title: Former Trump campaign manager Brad Parscale hospitalized following reported suicide attempt
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump's former campaign manager Brad Parscale was hospitalized Sunday following reports of a suicide attempt at his Florida home, CNN has learned.

value.title: New York Times: Trump paid no income taxes in 10 out of 15 years beginning in 2000
value.excerpt: Donald Trump has paid no income taxes whatsoever in 10 of the past 15 years since 2017 as a result of reporting that he was losing significantly more than he made, according to an explosive report released Sunday by the New York Times.

value.title: Watch live: Joe Biden delivers remarks in Delaware on Supreme Court
value.excerpt: Watch live coverage of Joe Biden as he delivers remarks in Wilmington, Del., on the U.S. Supreme Court.Sept. 27, 2020 © 2020 NBC UNIVERSAL

value.title: Pelosi says Trump is in a 'hurry' to confirm Barrett so she can partake in Obamacare case
value.excerpt: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi said Sunday that President Donald Trump is in a "hurry" to confirm his Supreme Court nominee so that the conservative jurist can participate in a highly consequential Obamacare case the court is set to hear days after the election.

value.title: Analysis: What America's European allies want from a Biden presidency
value.excerpt: Should Joe Biden win the upcoming US presidential election, his first and overwhelming foreign policy challenge will be winning back the trust of America's allies. value.title: Progressive activists are wary over criminal justice under a Biden-Harris administration
value.excerpt: They spent the summer on the frontlines of a historic protest movement against police violence. But many young criminal justice activists leading the charge for police reform won't be enthusiastically casting their ballots for the Democratic presidential ticket in November.

value.title: Trump and his envoys have trashed Europe's confidence in the US. The damage might be irreparable
value.excerpt: It's no secret that Donald Trump is no big fan of the European Union. Over the past four years, the US President has talked positively about Brexit and claimed that the bloc was created in order to "take advantage of the United States."

value.title: Trump unveils 'Platinum Plan' for Black Americans
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump unveiled a plan aimed at winning over Black Americans on Friday, less than two months before Election Day, largely expanding upon the existing economic-related initiatives the President established in his first term.

value.title: Trump targets Biden's lighter campaign schedule ahead of first debate
value.excerpt: Joe Biden's campaign at 9:20 a.m. ET on Thursday called a "lid" -- a term used to inform reporters that the Democratic presidential nominee wouldn't be making any public appearances for the rest of the day.

value.title: Trump foments mistrust of election he claims won't be honest
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump and top aides are responding to the uproar over his failure to guarantee a peaceful transfer of power by intensifying their efforts to create election chaos he can use to cling onto power should he lose in November.

value.title: White House touts unusual Justice Department announcement about 'discarded' Trump ballots in Pennsylvania
value.excerpt: The Justice Department said Thursday that it is investigating "potential issues with mail-in ballots" in the swing state of Pennsylvania and, in a highly unusual disclosure, revealed that several ballots marked for President Donald Trump were "discarded."
